The algorithmic aspect of the paper suggests that it belongs to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The combinatorial nature of the results and the use of graph theory techniques suggest that it could also belong to the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-category. The paper involves the analysis of algorithms and the complexity of computations, which are typical topics in the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category. The study of graph embeddings and the structure of minimal rooted trees suggest that the paper could also belong to the cs.CG (Computational Geometry) sub-category. Finally, the use of combinatorial optimization techniques and the study of extremal properties of graphs suggest that the paper could belong to the cs.GT (Combinatorics and Graph Theory) sub-category.
